  "clinical_criteria": [
    "Must be 731 days old or older",
    "Two or more relevant ICD-9 or ICD10 codes for intellectual disabilities in two or more in-person visits",
    "Controls must have two or more in person visits after 731 days old",
    "Visits must be for well child (pediatrics) for controls"
  ],
  "algorithm_summary": "This phenotype algorithm identifies cases of intellectual disability by requiring patients to be at least 731 days old with two or more relevant intellectual disability diagnosis codes (ICD-9: 317, 318.0-318.2, 319; ICD-10: F70-F73, F78-F79, R41.83) documented in two or more in-person visits. Cases are excluded if they have any codes from an extensive list of conditions that could cause secondary intellectual disabilities (including genetic syndromes, metabolic disorders, brain injuries, infections, etc.). Controls are defined as patients 731+ days old with no intellectual disability codes, no exclusionary codes, and at least two well-child visits. The algorithm captures both cases and controls with demographic covariates and other relevant diagnosis codes for analysis.",
  "analysis_timestamp": "2026-01-29T04:08:55.106999Z"
}